Tribal rebels in southwest Pakistan attacked a paramilitary convoy, killing three soldiers and injuring seven.
The rebels used light and heavy weapons, launching over 150 rockets and mortar shells.
The military deployed troops and helicopters to the area.
The clashes resulted in casualties, with conflicting reports on the number of tribesmen killed.
The violence escalated after previous rocket attacks, prompting thousands of troops to move into the region.
Fierce gun battles between rebels and Pakistani forces have left many dead and injured, leading to mass evacuations amid ongoing tensions and threats of further conflict.
